      "comment_id" : 101903197,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Fun thing is that the <code>replaceAll</code> method implicitly does <code>Pattern.compile(regex).matcher(testString).replaceAll(regexR&zwnj;&#8203;eplacementString)</code>! So, if you re-use the pattern this way, redundant objects will be avoided. Further, as @MarcelValdezOrozco says, making it static will prevent unnecessary pattern compile invocations.  :)"
